Goal
* Please change "1" to "01", "2" to "02" and "0" to "00" (otherwise, it feels like the digits are converted individually).

Thanks.

Code
* Alternative way (requested by author in their original code): use zfill and chr in two for-loops to populate the dictionary, one for-loop for the lowercase letters and one for-loop for the uppercase letters. (The space character is still added on its own.)

One for-loop is also possible.

To give you an idea (two-for-loop solution):
range(1, 27):
• str(1).zfill(2) = "01"
• chr(1 + 96) = "a"
• etc
range(27, 53):
• str(27).zfill(2) = "27"
• chr(27 + 38) = "A"
• etc

Or (one-for-loop solution):
range(1, 27):
• str(1).zfill(2) = "01"
• chr(1 + 96) = "a"
• str(1 + 26).zfill(2) = "27"
• chr(1 + 64) = "A"
• etc
